            <language langcode="eng">English.</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did><!-- TOP LEVEL METADATA GO HERE: -->
      <bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
         <head>Biography</head>
         <p>Macine Bartow, an author, was an editor at <title render="italic">Reader's Digest</title>.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>The collection contains correspondence from <persname>Fielding Dawson</persname> to <persname>Maxine Bartow</persname> from 1959  through 1990.  Also included are jacket proofs from several Dawson  publications, two black and white photographs (1958), the manuscript  of a short story, "Her Royal," written by Dawson, and several collections of poems by <persname>Robert Creeley</persname>.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a" id="a4">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection has been organized into three sections, determined by the format of the materials: Correspondence, Publications and Photographs.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
      	<head>Related Material</head>
      	<p>Archives &#x0026; Special Collections has a substantial collection of materials pertaining to literature, especially <corpname>Black Mountain College</corpname> and the individuals with which it is associated, in addition to a significant collection of Little Magazines.   See especially the Papers of <persname>Charles Olson</persname>, <persname>Fielding Dawson</persname>, <persname>Joel Oppenheimer</persname>, <persname>Robert Creeley</persname>, <persname>Ed Dorn</persname>, and <persname>Gregory Corso</persname>.  For detailed information on these collections please contact the <extref href="http://www.lib.uconn.edu/online/research/speclib/ASC/collections/curatorinfo.cfm?curatorid=6">curator</extref> or ask at the reference desk.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
      
      <separatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 0" id="a7">
         <head>Separated Material</head>
         <p>Monographs and magazines have been removed from the collection and will be cataloged.  Call numbers and locations will be provided in the Library's online catalog, HOMER.</p>
